But there's just one thing.

838
00:37:45,159 --> 00:37:48,199
I feel like you're always so busy,

839
00:37:48,199 --> 00:37:49,119
it's too hard on you.

840
00:37:49,119 --> 00:37:50,039
Too hard.

841
00:37:50,119 --> 00:37:52,559
In the future, when the business takes off,

842
00:37:52,559 --> 00:37:53,840
if you're the only one cooking,

843
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:54,920
it's just not realistic.

844
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:55,920
Not feasible.

845
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,719
Wait, what do you mean?

846
00:38:00,119 --> 00:38:01,559
I've been contacting

847
00:38:01,559 --> 00:38:02,840
a few chefs these past few days.

848
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,920
Their skill levels are quite high.

849
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:07,360
And their salary requirements

850
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,480
are also very reasonable.

851
00:38:08,639 --> 00:38:09,559
In the future,

852
00:38:09,559 --> 00:38:12,199
you'll be promoted to Head Chef Consultant.

853
00:38:12,199 --> 00:38:13,760
You'll order them around,

854
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,000
it's dignified and proper.

855
00:38:15,079 --> 00:38:17,119
Your skills can also be passed down.

856
00:38:17,840 --> 00:38:20,480
Big Brother, do you understand what he means?

857
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:22,559
He wants you to have an empty title.

858
00:38:22,559 --> 00:38:24,559
In reality, you won't enter the kitchen.

859
00:38:24,559 --> 00:38:25,360
Lianbao.

860
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:26,840
You're so unreliable.

861
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,480
You use my name for financing,

862
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:30,079
use Big Brother's name to open the shop.

863
00:38:30,079 --> 00:38:31,159
Is that what you mean?

864
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:32,199
Big Brother, don't listen to him.

865
00:38:32,199 --> 00:38:33,440
That's not what I meant.

866
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:34,639
I just think our project

867
00:38:34,639 --> 00:38:36,320
can't just sit idle forever.

868
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:38,039
We need to get moving, right?

869
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:42,000
All of you...

870
00:38:42,639 --> 00:38:44,239
Don't play these tricks with me.

871
00:38:44,719 --> 00:38:45,960
I'm putting my foot down today.

872
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:49,760
If you want to do it, fine.

873
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:52,039
If not, we disband.

874
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:54,960
Big Brother, no, Big Brother.

875
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:19,119
What are you doing?

876
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,719
Just documenting life.

877
00:39:20,719 --> 00:39:21,559
It's my habit.

878
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:27,599
Weiguo.

879
00:39:29,199 --> 00:39:31,199
I guess I can't finish writing this script.

880
00:39:31,199 --> 00:39:34,719
Your aunt insists I go buy groceries for her.

881
00:39:37,519 --> 00:39:38,280
So,

882
00:39:38,519 --> 00:39:39,800
keep me company for a stroll?

883
00:39:40,079 --> 00:39:41,440
I'd rather not go.

884
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:42,760
Grandpa Tong, I'll go with you.

885
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:44,480
I need to shoot some footage at the market anyway.

886
00:39:44,719 --> 00:39:45,719
Great, you two go.

887
00:39:45,719 --> 00:39:46,320
I have other things to do.

888
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:48,679
What's with your hot and cold attitude?

889
00:39:48,679 --> 00:39:49,719
Do I have to drag you?

890
00:39:49,719 --> 00:39:51,480
No, no, no. I'll go, I'll go.

891
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:52,800
Let's go.

892
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:55,559
Grandpa Tong sure knows how to handle you.

893
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:58,280
Let's go. Hurry up.

894
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:19,960
Also buy two jin of pork.

895
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,079
How much per jin?

896
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:24,559
Okay, okay, okay.

897
00:40:24,559 --> 00:40:25,840
Two... two jin of pork.

898
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:26,960
Got it, ma'am.

899
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:29,760
The old lady wants me to buy two jin of pork.

900
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:31,679
You two have fun here.

901
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:32,239
Will do.

902
00:40:32,239 --> 00:40:32,599
Have fun.

903
00:40:32,599 --> 00:40:33,079
Will do.

904
00:40:33,079 --> 00:40:33,920
Come over for dinner later.

905
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:34,519
Okay.

906
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,599
Some apples, please.

907
00:40:43,679 --> 00:40:44,400
Are they sweet?

908
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,000
Very sweet. Here.

909
00:40:50,199 --> 00:40:51,559
Pretty sweet. I'll take five jin.

910
00:40:51,599 --> 00:40:53,000
I never expected, Uncle Ma,

911
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,599
you had such a down-to-earth side.

912
00:40:54,760 --> 00:40:56,760
When I was a kid, I often went to the market.

913
00:40:57,239 --> 00:40:59,039
I remember an auntie at an apple stall

914
00:40:59,039 --> 00:41:00,360
who often peeled apples for me.

915
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:01,440
Just this taste.

916
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,480
Five jin.

917
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:04,159
Thank you.

918
00:41:04,159 --> 00:41:04,800
Here.

919
00:41:09,039 --> 00:41:10,559
These have handmade cloth soles.

920
00:41:10,559 --> 00:41:11,239
The quality is very good.

921
00:41:11,239 --> 00:41:12,360
You can try them on.

922
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:13,239
Old Beijing style.

923
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:17,559
Something else I saw as a kid.

924
00:41:18,159 --> 00:41:20,880
My mom bought them for me to wear when I was little.

925
00:41:22,239 --> 00:41:22,719
Thanks.

926
00:41:22,719 --> 00:41:23,599
You can try them on.

927
00:41:26,159 --> 00:41:27,039
Get me a pair.

928
00:41:27,039 --> 00:41:28,159
Okay, okay, okay.
